", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6766.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>The gradient of LP-Pooling is undefined when the sum of all inputs to the power of <code>p</code> is zero. The current implementation will yield NAN in this case.</p>\n<p>I've added a ReLU unit to set the gradient to zero if the sum of all input elements to the power of <code>p</code> is zero.</p>\n<p>This would fix issue <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"315908978\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6765\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6765/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6765\">#6765</a>.</p>", "body_text": "The gradient of LP-Pooling is undefined when the sum of all inputs to the power of p is zero. The current implementation will yield NAN in this case.\nI've added a ReLU unit to set the gradient to zero if the sum of all input elements to the power of p is zero.\nThis would fix issue #6765.", "body": "The gradient of LP-Pooling is undefined when the sum of all inputs to the power of `p` is zero. The current implementation will yield NAN in this case.\r\n\r\nI've added a ReLU unit to set the gradient to zero if the sum of all input elements to the power of `p` is zero.\r\n\r\nThis would fix issue #6765. "}